results.title: The Fountain of Goof FOG Tv Network The Cornfield
results.description:
The Fountain of Goof - F.O.G. Tv Network 
Presents: A 2017 Suspense Chipper/Thriller

The Cornfield - A spaghetti-western like chick-flick with a corny taste of humor.

Season 1
Episode 1:  The year: mid 1970's Location: San Diego, CA.

It's another quiet Saturday evening sitting with a glass of red wine, bag of chips and a lot of room left on her small, blue sofa...as Judy Long sits quietly in front of the boob-tube...eyes wide open...staring at the large black and white box sitting across the living room floor.  Her cold dinner that holds her partially eaten spaghetti waits to be cleared and cleaned.

Tho, her super carb filled dinner didn't satisfy her empty belly...the 2-3 glasses of wine along with her munchy/crunchies daily habit was her cherry on top desert for those often lonely evenings at home.

Episode 2:  Towanda 's Hat:

Out of nowhere,  she hears 3 soft, consecutive knocks...a few moments later...another 3 knocks. 

"Hmm, I'm not expecting any visitors...who on earth?"

She slowly and cautiously walks towards the front door and asks,

                            "Who is it?"  

The silent response made the hair on the back of her neck to stand.

Episode 3:  She hesitated after another set of knocks...again, no response.  Then, the beige desktop...door stopper sized telephone rang.  A sense of fear came over her...but...Julie gathered her inner strength...visualized putting on her "Towanda" cap and reached for the receiver.

                            "H-E-L-L-O?"  

she answered...prepared to Towanda-chop a quick wit response to whoever was on the other side of the phone line. 

At first, soft white noise...as tho...wherever the caller's location...was most likely standing near a breezy area...perhaps, right outside the front door?

Episode 4:  "Hello?"  Julie asked in a firmer tone.  "Who is there?" 

She heard a bag tear open...then...a loud crackling/crunching sound ...obviously creating very annoying junk-food eating noise...nothing else...just Crunching and Crunching...and...Crunching. 

 "Is this some kind of stupid joke?" she asked.

The rustling of whoever was holding the bag was obviously trying to taunt Julie.  Unknowingly, Towanda's inner-strength was about to be unleashed towards this Mr. Potato Head, corn-chip weird guy...alien...or whoever/whatever he was…

Perhaps, this was the legendary Mr. Munchy Crunchy Man of Mystery the entire town heard rumors about...but...no one had ever seen...sort of like America's Big Foot or El Hombre Sin Cabeza.  In this story, his name is:

                   ALVIN, The Chip Mouth

Episode 5:  Amid the long intervals of chewing, he finally whispers:


"Cornfield...Meet me...(crunching sounds)...at...the...Cornfield...(lip smacking sounds).  "Hmmm...Ok?"

                                   "C-O-R-N-F-I-E-L-D...!"

His voice was so powerful and mesmerizing, it set Julie into a trance-like state...into a potato/corn-chip craving frenzy.  Her past with junk food eating addictions quickly over powered all reasoning. 

Her body automatically froze...then, she turned towards the front door.  Step by step...bit by bit...inch by inch…her only goal was to reach the cornfield and get there Pronto!

Since the cornfield was approximately 50ft. from the farmhouse...she didn't put on a sweater or light jacket...not even shoes/slippers for that matter!

The wind felt a bit chilly and the full moon lit the path to her hypnotic destination.  The closer she walked towards the cornfield, the louder the sounds of munching, crunching and multiple bags rustling open could be heard.
 
A bright, yellow light illuminated from the center of the field...and...as she parted the last few corn stalks to see (in full view) where she was so hypnotically sent...Julie's eyes opened wide when she saw...the one and only...the legendary:

                                   ALVIN- The Chip Mouth

He smiled as he sat among his Mr. Potato Head corn-chip followers.  His appearance was larger than life...like the Lock-Ness Monster.  His paws...bigger than Big Foots...and...he wore a woman's cap that read:

                                   "T-O-W-A-N-D-A"

His 1970's psychedelic colorful painted thrown...a disco ball circulating in mid-air...and...music blasting from an old cartoon Tv show, Julie was immediately jolted awake when she heard a voice yell:

                                    “A-L-V-I-N!!!”

POOF!!!   Yikes!  Thankfullly, it was just some sort of a snap-crackle-pop rude awakening moment...a blast from the past potato chips/corn-chips nightmare from the days of her junk food junkie eating addictions/habits.

Eggster Monsalve
The Fountain of Goof (F.O.G.) Tv Network

p.s.  The Urban Coneboy in the picture displayed is Not for sale...just this F.O.G. Tv Network story called:  The Cornfield   Thx.

Support Operation Smile
